tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketones, glucose, bilirubin). Blood glucose and HbA1c are low, suggesting hypoglycemia and no evidence of chronic hyperglycemia. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease with nephrotic-range proteinuria and possible metabolic derangements. Prompt clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
